--- SCENARIO: smart ban — fuzzy/prefix resolves to one leader, shared names offer buttons ---
# /ban takes loose input. A unique match is applied silently to the status message (with a DM
# confirmation naming the leader, so the player can see how a partial/typo query was read); a
# query that matches several leaders comes back as buttons in DM instead of guessing wrong.
# Alice opens a private chat first so the bot can reach her there.

--- CHAT ---
alice: /lobby
ambotorix: <status *Lobby by @alice*>
alice: /setBanSize 2
ambotorix: <status *Bans per player: 2*>

--- DM (alice) ---
alice: /leaders                  # opens a private chat → DM-reachable
ambotorix: <button "{leader}">

--- CHAT ---
alice: /ban alex                 # prefix → unique → Macedon Alexander
ambotorix: <status *Bans:*@alice*Alexander*>   # the ban shows up silently in the status message

--- DM (alice) ---
ambotorix: ✅ Banned *Alexander*  # DM confirms which leader the partial query resolved to

--- CHAT ---
alice: /ban roosevelt            # one token, two leaders → must disambiguate, not guess

--- DM (alice) ---
ambotorix: *pick one to ban* <button "*Roosevelt*" x2 distinct>
